# Build and run the msgpack-haxe test suite on the C++ (hxcpp) target.
# This is the primary target for the library and exercises the type-coverage,
# decode-contract, Int64-dispatch and Node cross-language parity tests.
#
#   haxe tests_cpp.hxml
#
# Requires: haxe, the utest and hxcpp haxelibs, and a working C++ toolchain.
# The Node parity tests additionally need a `node` binary on PATH and an installed
# @msgpack/msgpack module (set MSGPACK_NODE_MODULE to its absolute path, or let the
# test walk up from the cwd to a node_modules/@msgpack/msgpack); when those are
# absent the parity tests SKIP rather than fail.
-debug
-lib utest
-lib hxcpp
-cp .
-cp tests
-main org.msgpack.tests.MsgPackTests
-cpp tests/cpp
-cmd echo "Running C++ tests..." && tests/cpp/MsgPackTests-debug
